{"tree":{"type":"node","kind":"SOURCE_FILE","width":11,"children":[{"type":"node","kind":"LET_BINDING","width":11,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"let","width":3},{"type":"token","kind":"WHITESPACE","text":" ","width":1},{"type":"node","kind":"IDENT_PATTERN","width":1,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"x","width":1}]},{"type":"token","kind":"WHITESPACE","text":" ","width":1},{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"=","width":1},{"type":"token","kind":"WHITESPACE","text":" ","width":1},{"type":"node","kind":"APPLY_EXPR","width":3,"children":[{"type":"node","kind":"ERROR","width":1,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"-","width":1}]},{"type":"node","kind":"INT_LITERAL","width":2,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"INT_LITERAL","text":"10","width":2}]}]}]}]},"diagnostics":[{"kind":{"id":"E0020","name":"missing-binary-operand","expected":"left operand for -","found":{"kind":"-","text":"-"},"fix":"add an expression before the operator","hint":"Binary operators like +, -, *, =, etc. require both a left and right operand.\n\nFor example:\n  ```ocaml\n  let x = 1 + 2   (* correct *)\n  let y = 1 +     (* missing right operand *)\n  let z = + 2     (* missing left operand *)\n  ```\n\nIf you want to create a partially applied operator function, use parentheses:\n  ```ocaml\n  let add_one = (+) 1\n  ```\n"},"span":{"start":9,"end":11}}]}
